## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v14 or higher)
- npm or yarn

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/ginesys-sales-manager.git
cd ginesys-sales-manager

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the development server
npm start
```

The app will open at `http://localhost:3000`

## 📱 Usage

### For Sales Reps
1. Log in with your name (no password needed)
2. Dashboard - View today's metrics and pending tasks
3. Activities - Log calls, demos, and meetings
4. DAR Sheet - Submit daily activity report
5. My Deals - Track your deals through the pipeline
6. My Tasks - View and complete assigned tasks
7. Leaderboard - See team performance rankings

### For Manager (Srinivas)
1. Log in as "Srinivas"
2. Dashboard - Get team overview and KPIs
3. Team Overview - View individual rep details
4. Pipeline - See all deals by stage
5. Task Management - Assign tasks to team members
6. DAR Reports - Review daily reports from all reps

## 💾 Data Storage

All data is stored in browser local storage. No backend server required.

## 🎯 Daily Activity Report Metrics

1. Calls Made
2. Demos Given
3. Negotiation Calls
4. Onsite Meetings
5. Online Meetings
6. Internal Meetings
7. Self Leads Generated
8. Leads Converted
9. Closures

## 📊 Sales Pipeline Stages

- **Lead** - New prospect
- **Opportunity** - Shows interest
- **Negotiation** - In active discussion
- **Closed Won** - Deal completed
- **Closed Lost** - Did not convert

## 🏆 Team Leaderboard Scoring

- Won Deal = 10 points
- Self Generated Lead = 5 points
- Activity = 1 point

## 🔐 Security

- No authentication backend (demo version)
- All data stored locally in browser
- Data persists even after closing browser

## 🚀 Deployment

### Deploy to Vercel (Recommended)

1. Push code to GitHub
2. Go to https://vercel.com
3. Click "New Project"
4. Select your GitHub repository
5. Click "Deploy"
6. Share your live URL with the team

